:: StoryTitle
Ashfall: Roads of Ruin

:: StoryData
{"ifid":"ASHFALL-ROADS-OF-RUIN","format":"SugarCube","format-version":"2.36.1"}

:: StoryStart
The wind howls, flinging grit against your visor. You huddle in the lee of a rusted husk that was once a transport truck. The storm is an ashfall, thick and choking, reducing the world to a grey-orange haze. Your fingers trace the edge of the charred parchment tucked inside your coat—the first fragment of a map to a myth. You need to find shelter, and fast.
[[Push forward into the storm->Outskirts-FirstShelter]]

:: Outskirts-FirstShelter
A low, reinforced structure emerges from the gloom, a pre-Cataclysm fallout shelter with a steel door slightly ajar. The groaning wind muffles all other sound. Something glints on the ground near the entrance—a discarded ration tin, recently opened.
[[Enter the shelter->ShelterInterior-MetMoth]]
[[Investigate the discarded tin->ShelterExterior-FoundTin]]

:: ShelterExterior-FoundTin
The tin is empty, but the lid is sharp. Scuffmarks in the ash lead away from the door, not inside. Someone was here moments ago and chose not to enter. They headed towards the jagged outlines of a ruined overpass.
[[Follow the tracks->OverpassRuins-MetMoth]]
[[Enter the shelter anyway->ShelterInterior-Alone]]

:: ShelterInterior-MetMoth
A young face peeks from behind a stack of crates, eyes wide. "Shhh! They're right outside," a voice whispers. It's a youth clad in patched fabrics, a courier's satchel slung across their chest. "The Legion's patrol. I barely slipped past." They introduce themselves as Moth.
[[Ask about the Legion->ShelterInterior-MetMoth-LearnLegion]]
[[Ask about the map fragment->ShelterInterior-MetMoth-LearnFragments]]

:: ShelterInterior-MetMoth-LearnLegion
Moth shudders. "Captain Bronn's men. They roll in on their land-trains, take what they want. They're looking for something... old tech, maps. They've been questioning everyone." The sound of heavy engines rumbles faintly through the walls.
[[Ask about the map fragment->ShelterInterior-MetMoth-LearnFragments]]

:: ShelterInterior-MetMoth-LearnFragments
Your fingers brush your map fragment. Moth's eyes follow the movement. "You have one? The Haven-0 shard?" they breathe. "They say there are three others. The Nomads whisper about them. The Legion wants them all." The engine sounds grow louder.
[[Suggest hiding until the patrol passes->ShelterInterior-WithMoth-Wait]]
[[Suggest making a run for it now->ShelterEscape-WithMoth]]

:: ShelterInterior-WithMoth-Wait
You and Moth press into the shadows as the steel door grinds open. Two Legion soldiers in scarred armor enter, flashlight beams cutting the dust. "Clear," one grunts. "Just vermin den." They leave, and the door clangs shut. You are safe for now.
[[Plan your next move with Moth->Crossroads-WithMoth]]

:: ShelterEscape-WithMoth
You burst from the shelter, Moth at your heels. The ash storm has eased slightly, revealing the hulking form of a Legion land-train idling nearby. Shouts ring out. "There! The courier and another!" A shot cracks past your head.
[[Run towards the ruined overpass->OverpassRuins-WithMoth-Chased]]
[[Try to lose them in a canyon of wrecked buildings->CanyonRuins-WithMoth-Chased]]

:: OverpassRuins-MetMoth
You find the courier, Moth, pressed against a concrete pylon, trying to light a small signal fire. They startle at your approach. "You... you're not Legion. I saw their patrol. I think they're looking for map fragments like yours." They seem anxious but hopeful.
[[Offer to travel together->Crossroads-MetMoth]]
[[Decide to go alone->Crossroads-Alone]]
:: ShelterInterior-Alone
The shelter is empty, cold, and silent. Dust motes dance in the slivers of light. You find a stale but edible protein bar in a broken locker. The rumble of engines fades into the distance. You are alone with your map and your thoughts.
[[Continue your journey->Crossroads-Alone]]

:: Crossroads-WithMoth
The storm has passed, leaving a world bleached grey. Moth points to three distinct paths. "West leads to Dustborn trails. East, the Technic Union outpost. North... that's Legion territory, but also the quickest route to the buried city the maps mention." The choices loom.
[[Head West toward the Nomads->NomadOutskirts-WithMoth]]
[[Head East toward the Technic Union->UnionOutpost-WithMoth]]
[[Risk the North route->LegionPatrol-WithMoth]]

:: Crossroads-Alone
The ash-laden air is still. Before you, the wasteland splits. A sign, half-buried, points west to "Dustborn Caravan Routes." To the east, a broken tower suggests a Technic Union relay. The northern road is scarred with tank treads. You must choose your path alone.
[[Head West toward the Nomads->NomadOutskirts-Alone]]
[[Head East toward the Technic Union->UnionOutpost-Alone]]
[[Risk the North route->LegionPatrol-Alone]]

:: NomadOutskirts-WithMoth
Wind-driven sand-skiffs glide over the dunes, their sails patched with vibrant cloth. Moth is recognized by a scout, who signals the caravan to halt. An elder named Kael approaches. "Moth! And you bring a stranger. Do you seek passage, or trouble?"
[[Ask for information on the map fragments->NomadCamp-WithMoth-LearnFragments]]
[[Offer to trade for supplies->NomadCamp-WithMoth-Trade]]

:: NomadOutskirts-Alone
A lone sand-skiff approaches, its rider wary. You stand your ground, hands visible. The rider, an elder named Kael, circles you. "You travel alone through the ash. A brave or foolish thing. The Dustborn offer trade to those who mean no harm. What is your business?"
[[Ask for information on the map fragments->NomadCamp-Alone-LearnFragments]]
[[Ask for safe passage->NomadCamp-Alone-Passage]]

:: UnionOutpost-WithMoth
A geodesic dome hums with power, surrounded by a fence of energized pylons. A voice crackles from a speaker. "Identify yourselves and your business." Moth speaks up. "Courier Moth, with a traveler. We seek knowledge." The gate slides open.
[[Enter the outpost->UnionLab-WithMoth-MetLyra]]

:: UnionOutpost-Alone
The Technic Union outpost is a stark contrast to the wastes. Clean lines and humming machinery. You are scanned at the gate before being admitted to a sparse reception area. A woman with intricate facial circuitry observes you coolly from a balcony.
[[Address the woman->UnionLab-Alone-MetLyra]]

:: LegionPatrol-WithMoth
You haven't gone a mile before a armored buggy skids to a halt, blocking the road. Two Steel Legion soldiers level rifles. "Halt! By order of Captain Hale. You will be searched." They glance at Moth's courier satchel with particular interest.
[[Submit to the search->LegionCheckpoint-WithMoth-Searched]]
[[Try to bluff your way past->LegionCheckpoint-WithMoth-Bluff]]

:: LegionPatrol-Alone
The tread-marked road is eerily quiet. Suddenly, a spotlight hits you from a watchtower ahead. "You! Stop where you are!" a voice barks. A gate swings open, revealing a Legion checkpoint. Resistance seems futile.
[[Comply with their orders->LegionCheckpoint-Alone-Searched]]
[[Attempt to flee->LegionCheckpoint-Alone-Flee]]

:: NomadCamp-WithMoth-LearnFragments
Elder Kael studies your fragment by firelight. "This script... it matches tales of the Skybreaker, the buried city. The second fragment was said to be held by an exile—a technomancer called Lyra. She is hunted by the Union and the Legion both." He points northeast. "She hides near the canyons."
[[Ask for a guide to the canyons->CanyonApproach-WithMoth-Guided]]
[[Set out immediately alone->CanyonApproach-WithMoth]]

:: UnionLab-WithMoth-MetLyra
The woman on the balcony descends. "I am Lyra Kade. The Union exiled me for my... predictions." Her gaze falls on the map fragment in your hand. "You have a shard of the old world. I can help you read it, but not here. The Legion is coming. Meet me at the Relay Station." She slips you a datachip.
[[Follow Lyra's suggestion->RelayStationExterior-WithMoth]]
[[Stay and deal with the Union->UnionLab-WithMoth-Stay]]
:: LegionCheckpoint-WithMoth-Searched
The soldiers find your map fragment. "Captain Hale will want to see this," one says, grabbing it. They take Moth's satchel too. "You're both coming with us." You are disarmed and forced onto their transport, heading deeper into Legion territory.
[[The journey to Legion HQ->LegionFortress-WithMoth-Captured]]

:: CanyonApproach-WithMoth-Guided
A Nomad guide leads you swiftly through hidden paths, avoiding ash sinks and Legion patrols. You arrive at the mouth of a deep canyon where the air crackles with static. "Lyra's place is in there," the guide says, nodding toward a cave entrance before turning back.
[[Enter the cave->LyraHideout-WithMoth-MetLyra]]

:: RelayStationExterior-WithMoth
The relay station is a skeleton of old-world comms towers, swaying in the wind. Lyra is there, working on a terminal. "Good. You came. The Union thinks I'm a rogue. The Legion thinks I'm a prize. But I know where the second fragment is—in the Skybreaker's core. We'll need the third to get there."
[[Agree to work with Lyra->RelayStation-WithMoth-LyraJoined]]
[[Demand more information first->RelayStation-WithMoth-Question]]

:: LyraHideout-WithMoth-MetLyra
Lyra Kade is surrounded by flickering holoscreens showing weather patterns. She looks up, startled but not surprised. "Moth. And you have the first fragment. I have the second." She points to a screen displaying a complex schematic. "The Legion is digging at Skybreaker. We don't have much time."
[[Propose an alliance->LyraHideout-WithMoth-LyraJoined]]
[[Ask for the fragment outright->LyraHideout-WithMoth-Refused]]

:: RelayStation-WithMoth-LyraJoined
Lyra integrates your fragment with her data. "The third fragment is likely with Dr. Oren Vale, the scientist who designed Haven-0. He's in Skybreaker, if he's still alive. The Legion will be there in force. Our only chance is to get there first." She packs a gear bag, ready to follow.
[[Travel to the Skybreaker foothills->SkybreakerFoothills-WithMoth-LyraJoined]]

:: LyraHideout-WithMoth-LyraJoined
Lyra hands you the second map fragment. It seamlessly joins with yours, revealing more of the path. "Together, we might just reach Skybreaker before Bronn Hale turns it into a fortress," she says. "The final approach is through a valley the Ashen Choir controls."
[[Begin the trek to Skybreaker->SkybreakerFoothills-WithMoth-LyraJoined]]

:: SkybreakerFoothills-WithMoth-LyraJoined
The buried city is a series of geometric shapes protruding from the ash like broken teeth. Legion excavation equipment swarms around the main entrance. Lyra points to a ventilation shaft on a cliff face. "That's our way in. Unconsecrated ground. The Choir won't guard it."
[[Ascend to the ventilation shaft->SkybreakerVent-WithMoth-LyraJoined]]

:: SkybreakerVent-WithMoth-LyraJoined
You squeeze into the dark, metal shaft, descending into the heart of the city. The air grows cold and stale. Below, you hear voices—not Legion, but chanting. You drop into a forgotten atrium where figures in grey robes circle a glowing console. The Ashen Choir.
[[Attempt to sneak past->SkybreakerAtrium-WithMoth-LyraJoined-Sneak]]
[[Confront the cultists->SkybreakerAtrium-WithMoth-LyraJoined-Fight]]

:: SkybreakerAtrium-WithMoth-LyraJoined-Sneak
You slip past the chanting cultists, finding a stairwell leading deeper down. Lyra whispers, "This leads to the old labs. Vale should be there." You emerge into a corridor lined with sealed doors. One door is slightly ajar, light spilling out. A faint sobbing comes from within.
[[Enter the room->ValesLab-WithMoth-LyraJoined-MetVale]]

:: SkybreakerAtrium-WithMoth-LyraJoined-Fight
The cultists turn, their eyes glowing with fanaticism. "Defilers!" they shriek. A brutal melee ensues. You and your companions fight your way through, but the noise alerts Legion patrols deeper in the facility. You reach a lab door as alarms begin to blare.
[[Break into the lab->ValesLab-WithMoth-LyraJoined-MetVale-Alerted]]

:: ValesLab-WithMoth-LyraJoined-MetVale
An old man in a stained lab coat huddles over a terminal, muttering to himself. He jumps at your entrance. "Oren Vale?" Lyra asks. He nods, terrified. "They're coming for my work. For Haven-0. It's real, but it's a choice... a terrible choice." He holds up the third fragment.
[[Convince Vale to join you->ValesLab-WithMoth-LyraJoined-ValeJoined]]
[[Take the fragment and leave him->ValesLab-WithMoth-LyraJoined-FragmentTaken]]

:: ValesLab-WithMoth-LyraJoined-MetVale-Alerted
Dr. Vale shrieks at the sound of alarms. "Too late! Hale is here!" The door bursts open, revealing Captain Bronn himself, flanked by soldiers. "The map, and the scientist. Now," he demands, weapon raised. You are surrounded.
[[Surrender the fragments->LegionVictory-Betrayed]]
[[Make a stand->LabConfrontation-FightHale]]

:: LabConfrontation-FightHale
The fight is chaotic. Vale is hit in the crossfire. Lyra manages to override a door lock, revealing an emergency exit tunnel. "This way!" she yells. You grab the third fragment from Vale's desk as Moth provides covering fire. You escape into the tunnels, but Hale's forces are in pursuit.
[[Escape into the deep tunnels->GeoCoreTunnels-WithMoth-LyraJoined-Fragment3-Pursued]]
:: GeoCoreTunnels-WithMoth-LyraJoined-Fragment3
The tunnels are hot, filled with the thrum of geothermal energy. This is the path to Haven-0. Lyra combines the three fragments on her wrist-comp. The full map appears, leading to a massive vault door ahead. "The final barrier," she says. "The purifier is inside."
[[Approach the vault door->Haven0Entrance-WithMoth-LyraJoined]]

:: Haven0Entrance-WithMoth-LyraJoined
The vault door is immense, covered in warning placards. As you approach, figures emerge from the shadows—Bronn Hale and his elites, having found another route. "It ends here," Hale snarls. "Give me the facility." From another passage, Ashen Choir fanatics appear, chanting for destruction.
[[Stand with Lyra and Moth to activate the purifier->Ending-Restoration]]
[[Side with Hale to seize control->Ending-Dominion]]
[[Give the facility to the Technic Union->Ending-Technocratic]]
[[Destroy the control console to prevent anyone from having it->Ending-Nomad]]
[[Join the Choir in their reverence for the ash->Ending-Ashen]]

:: Ending-Restoration
You fight a desperate rearguard action while Lyra works at the console. With a final, thunderous hum, the atmospheric purifier activates. A great wind begins to cycle through the arcology. High above, through a viewport, you see the thick ash clouds begin to thin, allowing a sliver of true sunlight to touch the earth for the first time in decades. The long winter is over.

:: Ending-Dominion
You lower your weapon and nod to Hale. His soldiers swiftly overwhelm the remaining cultists. The Legion seizes control of Haven-0. Bronn Hale places a hand on your shoulder. "You made the right choice. Order will be restored. Our order." The purifier is activated not to cleanse, but to control, dispensing clean air only to those who swear fealty.

:: Ending-Technocratic
You throw the access codes to Lyra. "The Union should have it," you shout. She inputs the sequence, and blast shields seal the Legion and the Choir out. Technic Union personnel pour in from hidden portals. The world will be saved, but only through the strict, unfeeling application of their science. Humanity is saved, but perhaps not its soul.

:: Ending-Nomad
You remember the words of the Dustborn, that some power is too great for any one hand. As Hale and the Choir clash, you smash the main console with the butt of your rifle. Sparks fly. Alarms wail. The systems go dark. Haven-0 is dead. The world remains poisoned, but free.

:: Ending-Ashen
The chanting of the Choir fills your ears, making sense for the first time. The ash is not a curse, but a testament to nature's power. You turn your weapon on Lyra's console, destroying it. The fanatics embrace you as one of their own. You walk out into the eternal fall, embracing the silence of the ruined world.
:: CanyonApproach-WithMoth
The canyon walls rise steeply around you, carved by ancient floods. The air is still and heavy with the smell of ozone. Moth points to faint scorch marks on the rock. "Lyra's tech leaves traces," they whisper. A narrow path leads upward toward a cave mouth, partially concealed by a rockfall.
[[Climb to the cave entrance->LyraHideout-WithMoth-MetLyra]]
[[Search the canyon floor for other clues->CanyonApproach-WithMoth-Search]]

:: CanyonApproach-WithMoth-Search
You scour the base of the cliff, finding discarded power cells and a shattered dataslate. Moth examines the fragments. "This is Union tech, but modified. She's close." A low hum emanates from behind a curtain of vines, revealing a hidden hatch instead of the cave above.
[[Enter through the hidden hatch->LyraHideout-WithMoth-MetLyra]]

:: CanyonRuins-WithMoth-Chased
Legion shouts echo through the narrow passages between collapsed buildings. You and Moth dart through skeletal frameworks, ash stirring with every step. A dead end looms—a wall of twisted rebar and concrete slabs. The only way is up, via a precarious-looking fire escape.
[[Ascend the fire escape->Rooftops-WithMoth-Chased]]
[[Try to hide in the rubble->CanyonHiding-WithMoth-Chased]]

:: CanyonHiding-WithMoth-Chased
You squeeze into a gap under a fallen girder, pulling Moth in after you. Legion boots crunch past, so close you can smell their lubricants. "Lost them," a soldier grunts. After a tense minute, the sounds fade. You emerge into an eerie silence, the patrol gone.
[[Continue toward the canyon->CanyonApproach-WithMoth]]

:: LegionCheckpoint-Alone-Flee
You spin and sprint back down the road. A shot rings out, kicking up ash near your feet. More shouts join the first. A Legion skimmer emerges from a side alley, its engine whining as it gives chase. The open wastes offer little cover ahead.
[[Dive into a drainage culvert->CulvertEscape-Alone]]
[[Try to outrun the skimmer on the open road->RoadEscape-Alone]]

:: CulvertEscape-Alone
The culvert is dark and choked with debris, but it swallows you whole. The skimmer screeches to a halt above, unable to follow. You crawl through the muck, emerging far from the checkpoint into a scrub-filled ravine. You are safe, but off-course.
[[Reorient yourself and continue->Crossroads-Alone]]

:: LegionCheckpoint-Alone-Searched
The soldiers pat you down with brutal efficiency. They find the map fragment. "Captain Hale's prize," one mutters, seizing it. You are shackled and thrown into the back of an armored transport. The vehicle lurches forward, taking you to the heart of Legion power.
[[The journey to the fortress->LegionFortress-Alone-Captured-NoMoth]]
:: LegionCheckpoint-WithMoth-Bluff
You step forward, projecting confidence. "Captain Hale is expecting us. We have information on Union movements." The soldiers hesitate, exchanging uncertain glances. One lowers his rifle slightly. "Is that so? The Captain didn't notify us of any informants."
[[Press the advantage->LegionCheckpoint-WithMoth-BluffSuccess]]
[[The bluff fails->LegionCheckpoint-WithMoth-Searched]]

:: LegionCheckpoint-WithMoth-BluffSuccess
"Check your comms," you insist. The soldier turns to his vehicle. In that moment of distraction, Moth gestures to a gap in the fence. You both slip through and melt into the ruins behind the checkpoint before they realize the deception.
[[Escape into the northern ruins->NorthernRuins-WithMoth]]

:: LegionFortress-WithMoth-Captured
The fortress is a converted pre-Cataclysm dam, bristling with guns. You and Moth are marched into a stark interrogation room. Captain Bronn Hale enters, a mountain of a man in polished armor. He places your map fragment on the table. "Now," he says. "Tell me where the others are."
[[Remain silent->LegionFortress-WithMoth-Interrogation]]
[[Try to bargain->LegionFortress-WithMoth-Bargain]]

:: LegionVictory-Betrayed
You serve the Legion in the new order, a ghost of your former self. You watch as the skies darken further under Hale's control. The purifier is a tool of oppression. Your name is forgotten, your hope extinguished. The ash falls eternal.
[[The world under the Legion->Ending-Dominion]]
:: LyraHideout-WithMoth-Refused
"You think you can just take it?" Lyra snaps, stepping between you and the fragment. "I didn't survive out here by being naive." Her hand goes to a device on her belt. The holoscreens flicker and die. "Get out. Before I make you."
[[Leave the hideout->CanyonApproach-WithMoth-Refused]]
[[Apologize and try again->LyraHideout-WithMoth-MetLyra]]

:: CanyonApproach-WithMoth-Refused
You retreat down the path, Lyra's glare burning into your back. The opportunity is lost. Moth looks at you, disappointed. "What now? We need that fragment." The path to Skybreaker seems much longer without Lyra's knowledge.
[[Return to the Nomads for another plan->NomadCamp-WithMoth-LearnFragments]]
[[Press on to Skybreaker without the second fragment->SkybreakerFoothills-WithMoth]]

:: NomadCamp-Alone-LearnFragments
Elder Kael listens intently as you describe your quest. He draws symbols in the sand. "The second fragment is sought by many. The Ashwitch, Lyra, may have it. She is not friendly, but she is just. Find her near the iron canyons. Do not go as a thief."
[[Ask for directions to the canyons->CanyonApproach-Alone]]
[[Thank him and leave->NomadCamp-Alone-Passage]]

:: NomadCamp-Alone-Passage
Kael gives a sharp whistle. A skiff is brought forward. "This will take you to the canyon's edge. No further. The winds are treacherous." You board the lightweight craft, and the Nomad pilot expertly navigates the dunes, leaving you at the mouth of the great chasm.
[[Enter the canyon->CanyonApproach-Alone]]

:: NomadCamp-WithMoth-Trade
Moth negotiates skillfully, trading salvaged components from their satchel for fresh water, filters, and information. "The Legion is digging at the buried city," a trader mentions casually. "They say an old man was seen there, a scientist." The fragment's destination becomes clearer.
[[Ask about the scientist->NomadCamp-WithMoth-LearnFragments]]
[[Prepare to depart for the buried city->SkybreakerFoothills-WithMoth]]

:: OverpassRuins-WithMoth-Chased
You scramble over broken concrete, Legion bullets pinging off the steel supports. Moth leads you to a collapsed section that forms a narrow bridge over a gully. "It's unstable, but it's our only chance!" they yell, already starting across.
[[Cross the unstable bridge->GullyEscape-WithMoth]]
[[Find another way down->OverpassDescent-WithMoth]]

:: GullyEscape-WithMoth
The bridge groans ominously but holds your weight. You reach the other side as the Legion soldiers stop at the edge, unwilling to follow. You slide down the gully's slope into a deep ravine, finally out of sight and out of range.
[[Catch your breath in the ravine->Ravine-WithMoth]]

:: RelayStation-WithMoth-Question
"I need to know what you're getting out of this," you demand. Lyra sighs. "The Union exiled me for predicting the Cataclysm. They called it heresy. I want to see the sky clear to prove I was right. And I want the Union to see it." Her motive seems genuine, if proud.
[[Accept her explanation->RelayStation-WithMoth-LyraJoined]]
[[Remain suspicious->RelayStation-WithMoth-Doubt]]

:: RelayStation-WithMoth-Doubt
"Words are cheap," you say. Lyra's face hardens. "Then go your own way. Try to find Skybreaker alone." She turns back to her terminal, shutting you out. The chance for an alliance evaporates in the static-filled air.
[[Leave the relay station->RelayStationExterior-WithMoth-Alone]]

:: UnionLab-Alone-MetLyra
The woman descends the stairs, her movements precise. "I am Lyra Kade. The Union monitors all travelers. You carry something of interest." Her eyes dart to a sensor display showing the energy signature of your map fragment. "That relic is dangerous. The Legion will kill for it."
[[Ask for her help->UnionLab-Alone-MetLyra-Help]]
[[Deny having anything of value->UnionLab-Alone-MetLyra-Deny]]

:: UnionLab-Alone-MetLyra-Help
Lyra leans closer, her voice dropping. "I can help you, but not here. The Prefect suspects me. Meet me at the abandoned Relay Station to the north. Come alone." She slips a small tracker into your hand. "It will guide you." She turns and walks away.
[[Follow Lyra's instructions->RelayStationExterior-Alone]]
:: UnionLab-WithMoth-Stay
"We should deal with the Union directly," you tell Moth. You approach a uniformed technician. "We wish to speak to your leader about the map fragments." The technician eyes you coldly. "The Prefect will see you now. But your weapons stay here." You are led to a secure chamber.
[[Enter the Prefect's chamber->UnionPrefect-WithMoth]]

:: UnionPrefect-WithMoth
The Prefect is a severe woman surrounded by data streams. "The Haven-0 fragments are Union property. You will surrender them for study." Armed guards step from the walls. "Resistance is pointless. The technology must be controlled for the good of all." There is no negotiation.
[[Surrender the fragments->UnionCustody-WithMoth]]
[[Attempt to fight your way out->UnionLabEscape-WithMoth]]

:: ValesLab-WithMoth-LyraJoined-FragmentTaken
You snatch the fragment from Vale's trembling hand. "Please, don't leave me with them!" he pleads. You ignore him, turning for the door. Lyra looks at you with disapproval but says nothing. As you leave, Vale's sobs fade behind you, alone with the approaching Legion.
[[Escape the lab->SkybreakerCorridor-WithMoth-LyraJoined-Fragment3]]

:: ValesLab-WithMoth-LyraJoined-ValeJoined
"We all go, or no one goes," you tell Vale. He nods shakily, gathering a few data drives. Lyra helps him to his feet. "The service tunnels," she says, leading the way. The four of you—Wanderer, Moth, Lyra, and Vale—disappear into the depths just as Legion boots echo in the hall.
[[Escape into the tunnels->GeoCoreTunnels-WithMoth-LyraJoined-ValeJoined-Fragment3]]
:: CanyonApproach-Alone
The canyon looms before you, a deep gash in the earth. The silence is profound, broken only by the skittering of ash-rats. Following Elder Kael's directions, you spot a narrow path winding up the cliff face, leading to a dark cave mouth. The air smells of ozone and decay.
[[Climb the path to the cave->LyraHideout-Alone-MetLyra]]
[[Search the canyon floor for another entrance->CanyonApproach-Alone-Search]]
:: GeoCoreTunnels-WithMoth-LyraJoined-ValeJoined-Fragment3
The geothermal tunnels are humid and loud, the air thick with the smell of sulfur. Dr. Vale clings to Lyra, unnerved by the primal energy. Moth scouts ahead, returning to report. "The vault door is just around the next bend. No signs of Legion or Choir yet." The final approach is clear.
[[Approach the Haven-0 vault->Haven0Entrance-WithMoth-LyraJoined-ValeJoined]]

:: LegionFortress-Alone-Captured
The fortress gates close behind you. Lyra is taken to a high-security cell. You are given a sterile room and a Legion uniform. Captain Hale grants you a title: "Liaison to Technical Assets." It is a hollow victory.
[[Serve the Legion->Ending-Dominion]]
:: LegionFortress-WithMoth-Bargain
"We can take you to the second fragment," you tell Hale. "The technomancer, Lyra, has it. But we need to be free to act as bait." Hale studies you, his expression unreadable. "A risky gambit," he says. "If you betray me, your death will be slow. But I am willing to gamble."
[[Accept the terms->LegionFortress-WithMoth-Released]]
[[Retract the offer->LegionFortress-WithMoth-Interrogation]]

:: LegionFortress-WithMoth-Interrogation
The interrogation is brutal, but you and Moth hold firm. During a transfer between cells, a distant explosion rocks the fortress—a Nomad sabotage raid. In the chaos, you break free from your guards and dive into a ventilation shaft, pulling Moth after you.
[[Escape in the chaos->LegionFortressEscape-WithMoth]]
:: NorthernRuins-WithMoth
You hide in the skeleton of a shattered library, shelves of rotting books tilting precariously. Moth checks the perimeter. "The Legion patrols are thinning out here. We can circle back toward the canyons or try for the Relay Station Lyra mentioned." The path is yours to choose.
[[Head for the canyons->CanyonApproach-WithMoth]]
[[Head for the Relay Station->RelayStationExterior-WithMoth]]

:: OverpassDescent-WithMoth
You find a precarious route down a twisted support beam, sliding into a gully filled with soft ash. The Legion fire goes high, missing you completely. You are safe for the moment, hidden in the deep shadow of the overpass. Moth signs, "Clear. Which way now?"
[[Continue toward the canyon->CanyonApproach-WithMoth]]
[[Head north toward the Relay Station->NorthernRuins-WithMoth]]

:: Ravine-WithMoth
You crouch in the deep ravine, listening as the Legion patrol moves away above. A small stream of brackish water trickles along the bottom. Moth catches their breath. "That was too close. We need to get off the main roads." The canyon lies to the east, the Relay Station to the north.
[[Go east toward the canyon->CanyonApproach-WithMoth]]
[[Go north toward the Relay Station->NorthernRuins-WithMoth]]

:: RelayStationExterior-Alone
