:: LegionCheckpoint-MetMoth-BluffSuccess
You present a convincing story about being Hale's scouts. The soldier with the scanner hesitates, then nods. "Codes check out. Proceed." He waves you through the checkpoint. You and Moth walk calmly past the barriers, not looking back until you are safely within the ruins beyond. The deception worked.
[[Continue into the northern ruins->NorthernRuins-MetMoth]]

:: LegionFortress-MetMoth-Captured
The fortress is a formidable structure of concrete and steel. You and Moth are marched into an interrogation room. Captain Bronn Hale enters, his presence filling the space. He places your map fragment on the table. "A courier and a wanderer. You have something I want. Tell me about the other fragments."
[[Remain silent->LegionFortress-MetMoth-Interrogation]]
[[Try to bargain for your freedom->LegionFortress-MetMoth-Bargain]]

:: NomadCamp-Alone-LyraJoined
Elder Kael listens intently. His eyes flick to Lyra. "The Ashwitch's presence is concerning. But the Legion is a greater threat. You may rest here for a night. No longer."
[[Accept the offer of shelter->NomadCamp-Alone-LyraJoined-Rest]]
[[Ask for supplies and continue immediately->NomadCamp-Alone-LyraJoined-Trade]]
:: NomadCamp-Alone-LyraJoined-Passage
Kael gives a sharp whistle. A skiff is brought forward. You board the craft, and the Nomad pilot navigates the dunes, leaving you at the edge of the geothermal badlands.
