[[Decline and leave->RelayStationExterior-MetMoth-Alone]]
:: SkybreakerFoothills-MetMoth
The buried city of Skybreaker looms in the distance, a series of angular shapes thrusting from the ash. Legion excavation equipment swarms around its base. Moth looks worried. "That's a lot of Legion. We need Lyra's knowledge to find another way in." The direct approach seems suicidal.
[[Search for an alternate route->SkybreakerFoothills-MetMoth-Search]]
[[Approach the Legion camp under a flag of parley->LegionExcavationSite-MetMoth]]

:: UnionLab-MetMoth-Stay
"We should speak with the Union leaders," you tell Moth. You approach a technician. "We wish to discuss the map fragments with your Prefect." The technician eyes you coldly. "The Prefect will see you. But your weapons remain here." You are led away from Lyra, deeper into the Union complex.
[[Enter the Prefect's chamber->UnionPrefect-MetMoth]]
:: CanyonAmbush-Alone-LyraJoined-Depart
You leave the three bound scouts behind. Lyra leads the way up a path out of the canyon. "They'll free themselves in a few hours. By then, we'll be at the vents."
[[Descend toward the vents->GeoCoreApproach-Alone-LyraJoined]]
:: CanyonAmbush-Alone-LyraJoined-Interrogation
Lyra applies a neural stimulator. The sergeant convulses. "Hale's main force... at Skybreaker... only patrols here..." he slurs. The information confirms your path is clear.
[[Continue toward the GeoCore vents->GeoCoreApproach-Alone-LyraJoined]]
:: CanyonApproach-MetMoth-Search
You and Moth scour the canyon's base, finding discarded power cells and a cracked dataslate. Moth examines the fragments. "Union tech, but modified. She's definitely here." A low hum draws your attention to a curtain of thick vines clinging to the cliff wall. Behind it, you find a sealed metal hatch, not the cave above.
[[Enter through the hidden hatch->LyraHideout-MetMoth-MetLyra]]

:: GeoCoreTunnels-Alone-LyraJoined
The tunnel entrance exhales warm, moist air. Inside, the passage glitters with sharp crystals. Lyra checks her sensors. "The main geothermal flow is this way. It's the most direct route."
[[Follow the main tunnel->GeoCoreTunnels-Alone-LyraJoined-Deeper]]
:: LegionExcavationSite-MetMoth
You approach the Legion camp with your hands raised. Sentries escort you to a large command tent. Captain Bronn Hale stands before a topographic map of Skybreaker. "A wanderer and a courier," he says, his voice dangerously calm. "You walk into my camp. That is either very brave or very foolish. Speak."
