"We can take you to the second fragment," you tell Hale. "The technomancer, Lyra, has it. But we need to be free to act as bait." Hale studies you, his expression unreadable. "A risky gambit," he says. "If you betray me, your death will be slow. But I am willing to gamble."
[[Accept the terms->CanyonApproach-MetMoth-Guarded]]
:: LegionFortress-MetMoth-Interrogation
The questioning is harsh, but you and Moth reveal nothing. During a shift change, an explosion rocks the fortress—a distraction. In the chaos, you overpower a guard and steal their key. You free Moth, and together you slip into a ventilation shaft, leaving the sounds of alarm behind.
[[Escape into the ducts->LegionFortressEscape-MetMoth]]

:: LyraHideout-MetMoth-MetLyra
The cave is a makeshift tech lab, holoscreens flickering with weather data. Lyra Kade spins around, a pistol in her hand. "Moth. And a stranger with a map shard." Her eyes are sharp, assessing. "The Legion is hours away. Why should I trust you with the second fragment? What do you offer besides trouble?"
[[Propose an alliance->LyraHideout-MetMoth-LyraJoined]]
[[Demand the fragment->LyraHideout-MetMoth-Refused]]

:: NomadCamp-Alone-LyraJoined-Rest
The night is cold, but the sense of temporary safety is a relief. You get a few hours of sleep, waking at dawn ready for the final challenge.
[[Depart at first light->GeoCoreApproach-Alone-LyraJoined]]
:: NomadCamp-Alone-LyraJoined-Trade
You ask for supplies, not sanctuary. Kael nods. The Nomads provide you with fresh water, food, and information. "The GeoCore vents are active. The path is dangerous, but clear."
[[Head for the GeoCore vents->GeoCoreApproach-Alone-LyraJoined]]
:: NorthernRuins-MetMoth
You and Moth hide in the skeleton of a pre-Cataclysm library, shelves of rotten books tilting around you. Moth checks the perimeter. "The Legion presence is light here. We can circle back toward the canyons or try for the Relay Station." The choice of path will define your next ally.
[[Head for the canyons->CanyonApproach-MetMoth]]
[[Head for the Relay Station->RelayStationExterior-MetMoth]]

:: RelayStation-MetMoth-MetLyra
Inside the shack, Lyra works at a terminal. "Your fragment and mine are two parts of a whole," she says without looking up. "The third is with Dr. Vale in Skybreaker. The Legion is already digging. We can work together, but we must move now." She finally turns, her gaze intense, awaiting your decision.
[[Agree to the alliance->RelayStation-MetMoth-LyraJoined]]
[[Refuse and leave->RelayStationExterior-MetMoth-Alone]]

:: SkybreakerFoothills-MetMoth-Search
You and Moth skirt the Legion's perimeter, keeping to the shadows of rubble and wrecked machinery. You find a collapsed ventilation grate, too small for armored troops. It's a tight, dark squeeze into the earth. "It might lead inside," Moth whispers, peering into the blackness.
[[Squeeze into the vent->SkybreakerVent-MetMoth]]

:: UnionPrefect-MetMoth
The Prefect is a severe woman surrounded by data streams. "The Haven-0 fragments are legacy technology. They belong under Union control for the good of humanity. You will surrender them." Armed guards step from the walls. There is no room for negotiation in her cold, logical world.
