You follow the gentle stream upstream, the blue moss providing an eerie light. The passage narrows, then opens into a domed cavern where the stream emerges from a crack in the rock wall. The air is fresh and cool. Carved into the cavern wall is a simple metal door, unmarked and seemingly ancient. It is unlocked. This is a forgotten back entrance.
